moveToNextStartTag

protected void moveToNextStartTag(boolean aAdvanceFirst)
                           throws org.xmlpull.v1.XmlPullParserException,
                                  java.io.IOException
This method moves the XmlPullParser forward towards the next start tag, or until an END_DOCUMENT is encountered - whichever comes first.

Parameters:
aAdvanceFirst - boolean to indicate whether the parser needs to move one position forward before checking for a start tag.
Throws:
org.xmlpull.v1.XmlPullParserException - when the XML parsing generated an error.
java.io.IOException - when the output file could not be read.

moveToNextStartTagWithEndBreaker

protected void moveToNextStartTagWithEndBreaker(java.lang.String aBreakingEndTag)
                                         throws org.xmlpull.v1.XmlPullParserException,
                                                java.io.IOException
This method moves the XmlPullParser forward towards the next start tag, or until the specified end tag is encountered - whichever comes first.

Parameters:
aBreakingEndTag - String that specifies the name for the overriding end tag.
Throws:
org.xmlpull.v1.XmlPullParserException - when the XML parsing generated an error.
java.io.IOException - when the output file could not be read.

moveToNextStartTagAfterTag

protected void moveToNextStartTagAfterTag(java.lang.String aAfterEndTag)
                                   throws org.xmlpull.v1.XmlPullParserException,
                                          java.io.IOException
This method moves the XmlPullParser forward towards the first start tag after the specified end tag, or until an END_DOCUMENT is encountered - whichever comes first.

Parameters:
aAfterEndTag - String with the name of the end tag that needs to be encountered first.
Throws:
org.xmlpull.v1.XmlPullParserException - when the XML parsing generated an error.
java.io.IOException - when the output file could not be read.
